batchListTokens(address[],uint8).details: Lists multiple tokens for the investor (caller)  If the token listing type is WHITELISTING, it will be whitelisted/allowed for the investor.  If the token listing type is BLACKLISTING, it will be blaclisted/disallowed for the investor.

params._addressType: can be WALLET(0) or ONCHAINID(1)  If it is WALLET, the token will be listed only for the caller wallet address  If it is ONCHAINID, the token will be listed for the ONCHAINID (it will be applied to all wallet addresses of the OID)  It will revert if the listing type of the token is not configured
params._tokenAddresses: is the array of addresses of tokens to be listed

batchUnlistTokens(address[],uint8).details: Unlists multiple tokens for the investor (caller)

params._addressType: can be WALLET(0) or ONCHAINID(1)  If it is WALLET, the token will be unlisted only for the caller wallet address  If it is ONCHAINID, the token will be unlisted for the ONCHAINID
params._tokenAddresses: is the array of addresses of tokens to be unlisted

configureToken(uint8).details: Configures the listing type of a token  Can only be called once per token

params._listingType: can be WHITELISTING(1) or BLACKLISTING(2)  WHITELISTING(1): investors must whitelist/allow the token address in order to receive it  BLACKLISTING(2): investors can receive this token by default. If they do not want to receive it,   they need to blacklist/disallow it.  Only the owner of the Compliance smart contract can call this function

getInvestorListingStatus(address,address.details: Returns the listing status of the given investor address for the token

params._investorAddress: the WALLET or ONCHAINID address of an investor to be checked  returns the listing status of the given investor.  If it is true:  - if the listing type of the token is WHITELISTING(1): investor can receive this token.  - if the listing type of the token is BLACKLISTING(2): investor can not receive this token.  If it is false:  - if the listing type of the token is WHITELISTING(1): investor can not receive this token.  - if the listing type of the token is BLACKLISTING(2): investor can receive this token.
params._tokenAddress: the token smart contract to be checked

getTokenListingType(address).details: Returns the configured listing type of the given token address

params._tokenAddress: the token smart contract to be checked  returns the listing type of the token:  NOT_CONFIGURED(0): The token is not configured for this module yet  WHITELISTING(1): investors must whitelist/allow the token address in order to receive it  BLACKLISTING(2): investors can receive this token by default. If they do not want to receive it,   they need to blacklist/disallow it.

initialize().details: initializes the contract and sets the initial state.

listToken(address,uint8).details: Lists a token for the investor (caller)  If the token listing type is WHITELISTING, it will be whitelisted/allowed for the investor.  If the token listing type is BLACKLISTING, it will be blaclisted/disallowed for the investor.

params._addressType: can be WALLET(0) or ONCHAINID(1)  If it is WALLET, the token will be listed only for the caller wallet address  If it is ONCHAINID, the token will be listed for the ONCHAINID (it will be applied to all wallet addresses of the OID)  It will revert if the listing type of the token is not configured
params._tokenAddress: is the address of the token to be listed

moduleBurnAction(address,uint256).details: See {IModule-moduleBurnAction}.  no burn action required in this module

moduleCheck(address,address,uint256,addr.details: See {IModule-moduleCheck}.  checks whether the _to address allows this token to receive  returns TRUE if the token is allowed for the address of _to (or for the OID of _to)  returns FALSE if the token is not allowed for the address of _to

moduleMintAction(address,uint256).details: See {IModule-moduleMintAction}.  no mint action required in this module

moduleTransferAction(address,address,uin.details: See {IModule-moduleTransferAction}.  no transfer action required in this module

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unlistToken(address,uint8).details: Unlists a token for the investor (caller)

params._addressType: can be WALLET(0) or ONCHAINID(1)  If it is WALLET, the token will be unlisted only for the caller wallet address  If it is ONCHAINID, the token will be unlisted for the ONCHAINID
params._tokenAddress: is the address of the token to be unlisted

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

initialize().notice: This function should only be called once during the contract deployment.
